	<h1>partical accelerators<sup><sup>&copy;</sup></sup></h1><hr />
	<h4 class="name"><u>by Ben</u></h4>
	<p><div class=indent>Partical accelerators are big tubes made for discovering what is inside if an atom.</div>
But the question is how do we figure out what is inside of an atom and how do they work?</p>
<p><div class=indent>


In the 1930's a person named <b>Ernest Lawrence</b> created the first partical accelerator.<br> The partical accelerator is used for discovering 
<abbr title="smaller particals that make up protons and nutrons"><u>quarks</u></abbr>.Partical accelerators move the small<br> group of atoms 11,000 circuits per second
</p></div>

</div>
