<div class="indent"> 
<p>Now how do they work. Partical accelerators use pole changing magnets to accelerate the <br><abbr title="particals that make up an atom">
sub attomic particals</abbr> allmost to the <abbr title="299 792 458 meters per seccond">speed of light</abbr> and try to smash the particals 
together. When they<br> shash the sub atomic particals together the quarks go diffrent ways and thats how they discover the <br>quarks, for example Up, Down, Top, 
Bottom, Strange, and Charm.</div>
